ace last year, I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think anyone had seen the eventual winner stopping mid-race and massaging their hamstring in a major race before,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Brasher added.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brasher,_New_York\", \"score\": 0.9691301660371875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brasher\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brasher,_New_York\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brasher,_New_York\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the most spectacular race\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"the eventual winner\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"mid\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"their hamstring\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"a major race\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New York City Marathon champion Tamirat Tola, plus Alexander Mutiso Munyao, Dawit Wolde and Kinde Atanaw headline a men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s race that is wide open in the absence of 2023 winner and world-record holder Kelvin Kiptum.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.247435786712103e-16, \"text\": \"New York City Marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\"}, {\"begin\": 1809, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tamirat Tola\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_